OL,4,Cmore people into poverty ` report
OL,6,FMortgage rate rises pushed an
OL,7,Festimated 320,000 more people into
OL,8,Fpoverty by the end of December 2023,
OL,9,Faccording to the Institute for Fiscal
OL,10,FStudies (IFS).
OL,12,FIn 2022/23, the average mortgage rate
OL,13,Fwas around 2.3%, translating to
OL,14,Finterest payments of #240 per month
OL,15,Ffor a household with a typical
OL,16,Foutstanding mortgage, a report from
OL,17,Fthe IFS said.
